msgid "finance"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.finance:1
msgid "Public-debt accounting and caps for new-build investment."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.finance:3
msgid ""
"Each new-tech investment carries a public-debt obligation equal to "
"``public_debt_ratio[te]`` times its discounted investment cost. The "
"module exposes that obligation as an indexed expression "
"``public_debt_newtech[y, z, te]`` and (optionally) caps the public debt "
"taken on each year, system-wide and per-zone:"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.finance:9
msgid ""
"{\\rm{public\\_debt}}_{y,z,te}\n"
"= {\\rm{cost\\_newtech}}_{y,z,te} \\times r^{\\rm{public}}_{te}\n"
"\n"
"\\sum_{z, te} {\\rm{public\\_debt}}_{y,z,te}\n"
"\\le \\overline{D^{\\rm{sys}}_{y}}\\quad\\forall y\n"
"\n"
"\\sum_{te} {\\rm{public\\_debt}}_{y,z,te}\n"
"\\le \\overline{D^{\\rm{zone}}_{y, z}}\\quad\\forall y, z"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.finance:20
msgid ""
"This module is OFF unless the user provides ``public_debt_ratio``; the "
"optional caps default to ``+inf`` (no constraint added)."
msgstr ""

